### FAL Provider

```
packages/fal/
├── src/
│   ├── index.ts (main export)
│   ├── version.ts
│   ├── fal-provider.ts (factory & main interface)
│   ├── fal-config.ts
│   ├── fal-error.ts
│   ├── fal-api-types.ts
│   ├── fal-image-model.ts
│   ├── fal-image-settings.ts
│   ├── fal-image-options.ts
│   ├── fal-image-model.test.ts
│   ├── fal-video-model.ts
│   ├── fal-video-settings.ts
│   ├── fal-video-model.test.ts
│   ├── fal-speech-model.ts
│   ├── fal-speech-settings.ts
│   ├── fal-speech-model.test.ts
│   ├── fal-transcription-model.ts
│   ├── fal-transcription-options.ts
│   └── fal-transcription-model.test.ts
├── package.json
├── tsconfig.json
├── tsconfig.build.json
├── tsup.config.ts
├── vitest.node.config.js
├── vitest.edge.config.js
└── CHANGELOG.md
```

---

## 10. KEY FILE NAMING CONVENTIONS

### Model Files
- `<provider>-<model-type>-model.ts` - Main model class
- `<provider>-<model-type>-options.ts` - User-facing options/types
- `<provider>-<model-type>-settings.ts` - Model ID types (FAL pattern)
- `<provider>-<model-type>-api.ts` - API request/response schemas

### Other Files
- `<provider>-provider.ts` - Main factory function and provider interface
- `<provider>-config.ts` - Configuration interface
- `<provider>-error.ts` - Error handling utilities
- `<provider>-<feature>.ts` - Feature-specific utilities
- `version.ts` - Version constant (injected at build time)
- `index.ts` - Main export barrel file

---

## 11. VERSION MANAGEMENT

**File:** `packages/fal/src/version.ts` (same pattern as OpenAI)

```typescript
declare const __PACKAGE_VERSION__: string | undefined;
export const VERSION: string =
  typeof __PACKAGE_VERSION__ !== 'undefined'
    ? __PACKAGE_VERSION__
    : '0.0.0-test';
```

The version is injected at build time via `tsup.config.ts`:
```typescript
define: {
  __PACKAGE_VERSION__: JSON.stringify(
    (await import('./package.json', { with: { type: 'json' } })).default
      .version,
  ),
}
```

---

## 12. EXPORT PATTERN (index.ts)

**OpenAI:**
```typescript
export { createOpenAI, openai } from './openai-provider';
export type { OpenAIProvider, OpenAIProviderSettings } from './openai-provider';
export type { OpenAILanguageModelChatOptions } from './chat/openai-chat-options';
export type { OpenAIEmbeddingModelOptions } from './embedding/openai-embedding-options';
export type { OpenAISpeechModelOptions } from './speech/openai-speech-options';
// ... type exports for all model types ...
export { VERSION } from './version';
```

**FAL:**
```typescript
export type { FalProvider, FalProviderSettings } from './fal-provider';
export { createFal, fal } from './fal-provider';
export type { FalImageModelOptions } from './fal-image-options';
export type { FalVideoModelOptions } from './fal-video-model';
export type { FalSpeechModelOptions } from './fal-speech-model';
export type { FalTranscriptionModelOptions } from './fal-transcription-model';
export { VERSION } from './version';
```

**Pattern:** Export both factory function and default instance, plus all relevant types

---

## 13. KEY IMPORTS & DEPENDENCIES

### Common from `@ai-sdk/provider`
- `ImageModelV3` - Image generation interface
- `LanguageModelV3` - Chat/completion interface
- `EmbeddingModelV3` - Embedding interface
- `SpeechModelV3` - Speech synthesis interface
- `TranscriptionModelV3` - Speech transcription interface
- `ProviderV3` - Base provider interface
- `Experimental_VideoModelV3` - Experimental video generation

### Common from `@ai-sdk/provider-utils`
- `postJsonToApi()` - Utility for JSON POST requests
- `postFormDataToApi()` - Utility for form data requests
- `getFromApi()` - Utility for GET requests
- `createJsonResponseHandler()` - Response parsing
- `createJsonErrorResponseHandler()` - Error handling
- `combineHeaders()` - Header utilities
- `loadApiKey()` - Environment variable loading
- `loadOptionalSetting()` - Optional setting loading
- `convertImageModelFileToDataUri()` - Image file conversion
- `downloadBlob()` - Image downloading
- `zodSchema()`, `lazySchema()` - Schema utilities
- `parseProviderOptions()` - Provider-specific options parsing

### Zod Usage
- `import { z } from 'zod/v4'` - Schema validation (v4 for compatibility)

---

## SUMMARY: PATTERNS TO FOLLOW FOR NEW PROVIDER

1. **Naming:** `@ai-sdk/<provider-name>`
2. **Provider Structure:**
   - `createProvider()` factory function
   - `ProviderInterface` extending `ProviderV3`
   - `ProviderSettings` configuration type
   - Export both factory and default instance

3. **Model Organization:**
   - One class per model type (Image, Chat, Embedding, etc.)
   - Separate options/settings files
   - Zod schemas for API responses
   - Error handlers for API failures

4. **Image Models Specifically:**
   - Implement `ImageModelV3`
   - Implement `doGenerate()` method
   - Return `{ images, warnings, response, providerMetadata }`
   - Handle `ImageModelV3File` for image editing/inpainting
   - Support `size`, `aspectRatio`, `n`, `seed` parameters
   - Validate feature support and add warnings

5. **Build & Config:**
   - Single tsup entry point (unless internal API needed)
   - Composite TypeScript project references
   - Both CJS and ESM outputs
   - Type definitions included
   - Source maps enabled
   - Version injection at build time

6. **Export Pattern:**
   - All types exported from `index.ts`
   - Factory function exported
   - Default instance exported
   - VERSION exported

---

These patterns ensure consistency across the AI SDK ecosystem and make it easy for users to work with multiple providers using a standardized interface.

