# Plan: Add `@ai-sdk/pixelart` Provider

## Context

The Vercel AI SDK uses a monorepo where each AI service is its own package under `packages/`. The task is to add a **new fictional image-only provider** called `@ai-sdk/pixelart` that:
- Only supports image generation (not text, chat, or embeddings)
- Exports a `createPixelArt` factory function and a `pixelart` default instance
- Supports provider-specific image settings: `style` (`"pixel"`, `"retro"`, `"8bit"`) and `pixelDensity`
- The standard `size` parameter (e.g., `"512x512"`) is forwarded directly to the API
- Uses `https://api.pixelart.ai/v1` as the base URL

The closest reference implementation to follow is **`packages/fal`** (also an image-only provider with no text/embedding support). The new package must not modify any existing provider packages.

